<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFE4FFDBFCD62938F1EEFBC5" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="312" pageId="19" pageNumber="308" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFE4FFDBFCD62938F3D4FCC5" blockId="19.[828,1437,1574,2078]" lastBlockId="23.[151,760,190,1077]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="312" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFCD62938F2A1F9EE" bold="true" box="[828,944,1574,1598]" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae brown. Antennomere II longer than III. Pronotum with smoky stripe not reaching posterior margin. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFC162999F541F94E" box="[1020,1104,1671,1694]" captionStart="Figs 4" captionStartId="5.[150,187,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[247,1334,221,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-16@5.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 4A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys immaculatus sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177535/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth and almost half of third rostral segment (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFC1D29D9F54AF90E" box="[1015,1115,1735,1758]" captionStart="Figs 17" captionStartId="22.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[178,1401,220,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-43@22.[740,1027,1075,1363]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 17A–F. Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process.Arrow indicates the lateral projection of the dorsal rim. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177559/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Fig. 17F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFB9B29D8F40CF90E" bold="true" box="[1137,1309,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFCA929F9F2C1F92E" box="[835,976,1767,1790]" captionStart="Figs 17" captionStartId="22.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[178,1401,220,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-43@22.[740,1027,1075,1363]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 17A–F. Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process.Arrow indicates the lateral projection of the dorsal rim. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177559/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 17A–D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal rim with small lateral projection rounded close to posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFB0A2819F452F8CE" box="[1248,1347,1799,1822]" captionStart="Figs 17" captionStartId="22.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[178,1401,220,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-43@22.[740,1027,1075,1363]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 17A–F. Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process.Arrow indicates the lateral projection of the dorsal rim. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177559/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
, arrow). Posterolateral angles developed, rounded, and straight (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFA982839F27DF88E" captionStart="Figs 17" captionStartId="22.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[178,1401,220,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-43@22.[740,1027,1075,1363]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 17A–F. Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process.Arrow indicates the lateral projection of the dorsal rim. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177559/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup parallel to dorsal rim, short, narrow, slightly concave medially; inner (proximal) part truncate, ventral angle with dentiform process; outer (distal) part tongue-like and enlarged, dorsal margin tumid (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFCA928D9F2D4F80E" box="[835,965,1991,2014]" captionStart="Figs 17" captionStartId="22.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[178,1401,220,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-43@22.[740,1027,1075,1363]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 17A–F. Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process.Arrow indicates the lateral projection of the dorsal rim. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177559/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 17C,D</figureCitation>
). Paramere with two lobes; both lobes long and rounded distally, resembling whale tail; anterior lobe directed to base of proctiger (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFB992719F5E2F7CE" box="[1139,1267,2055,2078]" captionStart="Figs 17" captionStartId="22.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[178,1401,220,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-43@22.[740,1027,1075,1363]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 17A–F. Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process.Arrow indicates the lateral projection of the dorsal rim. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177559/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 17C,D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with tufts of long setae along lateral excavation; posterior face subpentagonal (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFED42FC0F0ACFF25" box="[318,445,222,245]" captionStart="Figs 17" captionStartId="22.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[178,1401,220,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-43@22.[740,1027,1075,1363]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 17A–F. Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process.Arrow indicates the lateral projection of the dorsal rim. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177559/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Figs 17C,D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions triangular, short, distally blunt, inner lateral face not excavated, dorsal side without dark spot; slightly surpassing level of posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFE272E20F33AFE85" box="[461,555,318,341]" captionStart="Figs 17" captionStartId="22.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[178,1401,220,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-43@22.[740,1027,1075,1363]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 17A–F. Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process.Arrow indicates the lateral projection of the dorsal rim. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177559/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 17B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE0FFDBFDD62E23F3E9FE85" bold="true" box="[572,760,317,341]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Genital plates (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE0FFDBFED42E40F0B1FEA5" box="[318,416,350,373]" captionStart="Figs 17" captionStartId="22.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[178,1401,220,2017]" captionTargetId="figure-43@22.[740,1027,1075,1363]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 17A–F. Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process.Arrow indicates the lateral projection of the dorsal rim. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177559/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Fig. 17E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 without dentiform angles, posterior margin almost straight, barely slanting; imaginary line tangent to posterior margin not reaching medial line of valvifers 9; excavation V-shaped. Valvulae 8 exposed. Apices of laterotergites 8 above level of apices of abdominal segment VII. Laterotergites 9 surpassing band connecting laterotergites 8; apices almost reaching imaginary line tangent to apices of abdominal segment VII. 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE0FFDBFF5F2D40F047FDA5" bold="true" box="[181,342,606,629]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">Measurements</emphasis>
(n = 2; 
<typeStatus id="6C50885EFFE0FFDBFE4E2D40F310FDA5" box="[420,513,606,629]" pageId="23" pageNumber="312">holotype</typeStatus>
